text: Warriors just don't look right. Only 41 first-half points. Still awkward and icy between KD and Draymond. Unfixable. Will keep bubbling to surface. This is good news for the West, especially for the LeLakers.
Blind Witnesses: You're really throwing a parade for LeBron for passing Wilt Chamberlain on the scoring list? LeBron has played 112 more games than Wilt did!

I project LeBron will pass The Greatest Player ever on the scoring list in 32 more games, on Thursday night, Jan. 17 in (fittingly) my hometown of OKC. On that night, LeBron will have played 85 more games than Michael Jordan did. Give LeBron the Durability and Longevity Award!

Interesting that KD and Draymond appeared to have a nice exchange, but KD was nicely chiding him for not giving up the ball before traveling. KD is all-time sensitive. He will not be able to get over being called a "b" by an angry Draymond.

If only Tom Brady had Aaron Rodgers' receiving corps & run game. If only Brady had a Davante, a J Graham, an Aaron Jones, a Valdes-Scantling, an Equanimeous, even a Tonyan. If only Brady had a defense like the Pack Sack Attack. (Brady is 7-3, Rodgers 4-4-1 with a loss to Brady).

Aaron Rodgers is on pace to shatter his own NFL record for throwaways. Isn't throwing it away to avoid sacks - still sacked 7th most. He's protecting stats - now 17 TDs to 1 INT. Won't try to make a risky play. Why he's 22nd in QBR and 4-4-1. If he loves it, he cool-whips it.

Aaron Rodgers is the LeBron James of the NFL, so overhyped for spectacular games instead of results. Rodgers played in (and won) one Super Bowl NINE YEARS AGO! Since, he's 5-6 in playoffs. The 5 wins: Joe Webb, Dez catch, KirkCousins, Giants boat trip, Mason Crossbar from 56 & 51
The Rockets look unclogged minus Melo. Still not the defensive team they became last year. But so much freer on offense.
Good throw by Aaron Rodgers to a top 10 receiver. Slightly underthrown. Great concentration by Davante to haul it in despite a near breakup by Shaq Griffin. Huge play.
I love to watch Russell Wilson operate at QB ... unless it's against the Cowboys.

Obviously Mike McCarthy will get blamed for this loss for not challenging the big completion to Lockett, which was not a catch. Look for ARodg to subtly blame him. At this rate McCarthy will be Baker Mayfield's head coach next year.
I wonder how Shannon Sharpe will defend Aaron Rodgers after the Packers punted four times and managed only a field goal in the second half?
